⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Dorian Havilliard
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Dorian Havilliard:M1:4dd9ee⟧

WHO   — Dorian Havilliard — Crown Prince of Adarlan · the conqueror's reluctant heir
WHAT  — A secondary protagonist of Throne of Glass — the prince who pulls an assassin out of the salt mines to be his Champion, and finds himself drawn to her against every rule his crown demands.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — The Assassin's Blade & book one  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a conscience is a dangerous thing to keep in a tyrant's house; because he would rather be loved than feared, and rather be free than be his father's heir; because she is the first person who sees the man and not the title.
HOW   — By wit and easy charm and a library's worth of reading; by a quiet courage that defies the King in small, costly ways; by choosing Celaena from Endovier and standing closer to her than a crown prince ever should.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the heir of Adarlan — but I will not be the man my father made the world fear.

